netBotz_dev_gateway.name: netBotz_dev_gateway
netBotz_dev_gateway.description: Netbotz device's default gateway/router. 0.0.0.0 if not defined.

netBotz_dev_primarydns.name: netBotz_dev_primarydns
netBotz_dev_primarydns.description: Primary Domain Name Server. 0.0.0.0 if not defined.

netBotz_dev_secondarydns.name: netBotz_dev_secondarydns
netBotz_dev_secondarydns.description: Secondary Domain Name Server. 0.0.0.0 if not defined.

netBotz_dev_smtp.name: netBotz_dev_smtp
netBotz_dev_smtp.description: SMTP server address. This is the mail server used for sending alert e-mails.

netBotz_dev_smtpport.name: netBotz_dev_smtpport
netBotz_dev_smtpport.description: SMTP port. Port number of SMTP server used for sending alert e-mails.

netBotz_dev_loglevel.name: netBotz_dev_loglevel
netBotz_dev_loglevel.description: This field contains the log level of the Netbotz device. Log messages will be filtered, so that only same or lower-level messages will be passed. The default log level is 5, for warnings and lower levels. The log levels are the following: 1 - emergency 2 - alert 3 - critical 4 - error 5 - warning 6 - notice 7 - info 8 - trace

netBotz_dev_logaddress.name: netBotz_dev_logaddress
netBotz_dev_logaddress.description: This field contains an IP address to receive log messages from the Netbotz device. 0.0.0.0 for no external logging.

netBotz_dev_logport.name: netBotz_dev_logport
netBotz_dev_logport.description: Port to use in conjunction with the log address, for log messages from the Netbotz device to be sent to an external IP address. 0 = no external logging.

netBotz_dev_primaryemail.name: netBotz_dev_primaryemail
netBotz_dev_primaryemail.description: The primary email addresses for alerts and messages (list separated by commas for multiple addresses).

netBotz_dev_secondaryemail.name: netBotz_dev_secondaryemail
netBotz_dev_secondaryemail.description: The secondary email address for alerts and messages (list separated by commas for multiple addresses).

netBotz_dev_pager.name: netBotz_dev_pager
netBotz_dev_pager.description: The pager number for alerts and messages. Currently, not used.

netBotz_dev_serialno.name: netBotz_dev_serialno
netBotz_dev_serialno.description: The serial number of the Netbotz device.

netBotz_dev_pop.name: netBotz_dev_pop
netBotz_dev_pop.description: POP server name. Currently, not used.

netBotz_dev_version.name: netBotz_dev_version
netBotz_dev_version.description: The current NetBotz device firmware version.

netBotz_dev_registered.name: netBotz_dev_registered
netBotz_dev_registered.description: Indicates if the device has been registered with Netbotz, Inc. 1=registered, 0=not registered.

netBotz_default_applet.name: netBotz_default_applet
netBotz_default_applet.description: Setting to control if default web page should launch applet by default(1) or the HTML status page(0).

netBotz_guibar_color.name: netBotz_guibar_color
netBotz_guibar_color.description: Setting for color of GUI bar (RGB). Value = 0xRRGGBB.

netBotz_locale.name: netBotz_locale
netBotz_locale.description: The locale ID of the NetBotz device. Format is ISO 639 language (lower case), an underscore, and ISO 3166 country (upper case). Some locales are just the ISO 639 language code.

netBotz_timezone.name: netBotz_timezone
netBotz_timezone.description: The timezone ID of the NetBotz device.

netBotz_24hourpreferred.name: netBotz_24hourpreferred
netBotz_24hourpreferred.description: Indicates if 24-hour(1) versus 12-hour(0) time format is preferred.

netBotz_utc_clock.name: netBotz_utc_clock
netBotz_utc_clock.description: Current time of clock on NetBotz device, in UTC seconds (seconds since 1/1/1970 12:00am GMT).

netBotz_ismetric.name: netBotz_ismetric
netBotz_ismetric.description: Units are metric (1) or U.S. (0). Applies to temperature and airflow rate.

netBotz_alert_url.name: netBotz_alert_url
netBotz_alert_url.description: The URL, if defined, to which non-picture alerts are HTTP POSTed

netBotz_picture_alert_url.name: netBotz_picture_alert_url
netBotz_picture_alert_url.description: The URL, if defined, to which picture alerts are HTTP POSTed, using multipart/form-data encoding.

netBotz_sensor_data_url.name: netBotz_sensor_data_url
netBotz_sensor_data_url.description: The URL, if defined, to which sensor data is periodically HTTP POSTed.

netBotz_alert_url_logon.name: netBotz_alert_url_logon
netBotz_alert_url_logon.description: The user ID and password, if defined, used for POSTing non-picture alerts. Field is write-only, and formatted <username>/<password>

netBotz_picture_alert_url_logon.name: netBotz_picture_alert_url_logon
netBotz_picture_alert_url_logon.description: The user ID and password, if defined, used for POSTing picture alerts. Field is write-only, and formatted <username>/<password>

netBotz_sensor_data_url_logon.name: netBotz_sensor_data_url_logon
netBotz_sensor_data_url_logon.description: The user ID and password, if defined, used for POSTing sensor data. Field is write-only, and formatted <username>/<password>

netBotz_sensor_data_url_period.name: netBotz_sensor_data_url_period
netBotz_sensor_data_url_period.description: Default number of minutes between periodic sensor data HTTP POSTs.

netBotz_sensor_data_url_flags.name: netBotz_sensor_data_url_flags
netBotz_sensor_data_url_flags.description: Option flags for data POSTs of sensor data. Bit 0=1 if current picture should be included. Bits 1-31 are reserved.
